Senior Finance Analyst - 6-Month Contract

Sydney | Large-Scale Transformation Program | Immediate Start

The company

Join a major ASX-listed financial services organisation with a strong presence across Australia and a reputation for driving innovative, enterprise-wide transformation. This is a business known for its collaborative culture, commercial maturity, and commitment to modernising its core operations. You'll be stepping into a high-performing environment where your work directly influences strategic decision-making at scale.

The role

Sitting within a large modernisation program, this role will see you act as a key finance partner responsible for developing, enhancing, and owning complex financial models that support strategic change.
You will work closely with senior program, finance, and business stakeholders to translate challenging commercial questions into clear, accurate, and scalable financial insights.

Key responsibilities include:

Designing, building, and optimising complex financial models for cost-benefit analysis, scenario planning, and program-wide financial tracking.


Refreshing or rebuilding existing benefits models to support an enterprise modernisation program.


Developing a robust cost management model to track actuals, budgets, and forecasts.


Conducting sensitivity analysis and scenario modelling to support strategic decision-making.


Presenting insights, risks, and recommendations to senior leaders.



Technical capability

Advanced Excel skills, including complex formulas and scenario modelling (macros/VBA advantageous).

Experience within the insurance sector or a similar regulated financial services environment is desired.


Prior experience in management consulting, strategy advisory, or large-scale transformation programs.


Exposure to Power BI, Tableau, or similar data visualisation tools is beneficial.



Qualifications

Relevant tertiary degree and accounting qualification (CA/CPA or equivalent).

You will work with national stakeholder groups to gather requirements, run workshops and translate business needs into technical documentation for development teams. You will maintain up-to-date process documentation and contribute to a continuous improvement culture.

To be successful you will bring:

4 - 7 years of business analysis or process improvement experience
Experience in professional services or consultancy desirable
Ability to run workshops in person and remotely
Strong requirements gathering and documentation skills
Understanding of AI technologies and their application in operations
Proficiency in Excel, SQL, Power BI or similar tools
Knowledge of Lean, Six Sigma or other improvement frameworks
Experience with Prince2 or Agile Scrum
Familiarity with MS Project, Planner, Jira and Confluence
A relevant Bachelorâ€™s degree
This role offers exposure to senior leaders, complex improvement initiatives and the opportunity to influence firm-wide operational outcomes.

If this role is of interest, please apply.
